Class CSVWriter

java.lang.Object
Controller.CSVWriter
public class CSVWriter extends Object
Utility class for writing various types of data to CSV files.

The CSVWriter class provides static methods for writing data to CSV files for different entities within the application. These entities include applicants, HDB managers, officers, BTO projects, enquiries, flat bookings, BTO applications, and registrations. Each method is responsible for converting the list of entities into a CSV format and writing it to a specified file path.

Each method handles the creation of a BufferedWriter to write the respective entity data to the CSV file, ensuring proper formatting by writing headers and data lines. In case of an IOException, the error is printed to the standard error stream.

The following methods are provided for writing different types of data:

  • writeApplicantCSV(String, Applicant_list)
  • writeHDBManagerCSV(String, HDBManager_List)
  • writeHDBOfficerCSV(String, HDBOfficer_List)
  • writeBTOProjectCSV(String, BTOProject_List)
  • writeEnquiryCSV(String, Enquiry_List)
  • writeFlatBookingCSV(String, FlatBooking_List)
  • writeBTOApplicationCSV(String, BTOApplication_List)
  • writeRegistrationCSV(String, Registration_List)

The data for each entity is formatted as a comma-separated string and written as a new line in the output file.
